title: Who will win the 2020 Georgia Democratic primary?
preds: Well?  Just came across this question. Better late than never.

Change: Joe (+3), Someone Else (-5), Warren (+1), Sanders (+1) As the election gets closer the probability of tail events decreases. Additionally, I updated my priors. While before I believed if not Joe Biden the party would put someone else on the ballot I now realize that it would have to be someone already on the ballot.

It is almost certain that Joe Biden will win the Democratic primary in Georgia. This is due to all the other Democratic candidates leaving the race. Former Democratic candidates have also endorsed Joe Biden, including Bernie Sanders, Pete Buttigieg and Elizabeth Warren.
This is entirely the probability of Joe dying of corona or getting embarrassed off the ballot. Current allegations against him are serious but probably not good enough.
Joe Biden is the overwhelming favorite, however, in the midst of this outbreak, we have to account for the probability that health complications pull him from the ballot.

Joe Biden has been consistently leading the Georgia polls since last July when he was polling at around 30% with the closest follower being Kamala Harris at 15%. Now, several dropouts later, Vice President Biden is polling at about 60% with the only other candidate, Senator Bernie Sanders, polling about half at 30%. Georgia is a more conservative state, so choosing Bernie Sanders as the candidate is extremely unlikely. In addition, there has been very little news coverage on the democratic primary since the outbreak of Covid-19, which will likely lead to  less information being spread on Bernie Sanders' platform, therefore more voters choosing Biden, who they know. The counterfactual, while unlikely, is a large scale movement for more social policies due to Covid-19, prompting voters to support a more socialist Bernie Sanders.
I think Biden will be the chosen rep

Biden looks to have a high chance, but if he or Sanders get sick it may end up with all kinds of weird results, so have not put anyone at zero and having a new candidate pop up is not out of the realms of possibility.  also have bumped up Sanders from 15 to 30pc chance because as people get sick they may increasing like his healthcare proposals.

The only scenario I can see anyone but Joe Biden winning Georgia is if his campaign somehow self-implodes in which case Bernie Sanders as the only other major candidate running would be the prohibitive favorite. Only exception would be if Joe Biden had such a complete collapse that it prompted another candidate of the democratic elite to run (ex. Hillary Clinton). The most likely campaign ruining event for Biden is the Arizona debate where Biden will be forced to debate for extended stretches, something he has largely avoided in the previously crowed debate stages.
Still want to see who Warren decides to endorse
Strong showing recently for Biden, although Sanders also surging in poll.  Biden keeping ahead so far.  Expecting to require refined forecast over next few days.

Joe Biden has convincingly won all southern states so far in this primary season. He is riding a massive wave of momentum coming off of his strong Super Tuesday results. He has strong support from Black Democrats, having won 72% percent of black voters in neighboring Alabama according to exit polls. In Alabama, Biden won every single county and won over 63% of the vote. Georgia is very demographically similar to Alabama, in fact it has an even lower percentage of white residents. If each demographic group in Georgia votes similarly to Alabama (and Sc), and I see no reason not too, then Biden will easily win Georgia. Additionally, Michael Bloomberg has dropped out meaning there is only one centrist/moderate candidate left.
